He be-&thorn;ou&yogh;te him on monnes soule hou hit scholde be lost wi&thorn;-outen ende but
he diede &thorn;erfore, and hou he schulde &thorn;e nexte day after &thorn;at ben honged on &thorn;e
roode-tree; and he was in a gret agonye as no wonder was, and for drede of
deth he swatte dropes of blood, &thorn;e w&yogh;uche trilleden doun of his bodi to &thorn;e
eor&thorn;e as watur do&thorn; of an hous after reyn, and &thorn;enne preyede he to his ffader
&amp; seide: &laquo;A, ffader, &yogh;if hit may be, let me not dye &thorn;us dispitousliche.  No&thorn;eles, he sei&thorn;, &thorn;i wille beo don and not myn&raquo;.  And &thorn;enne com he a&yogh;eyn to his disciples &amp; fond hem slepynge, and &thorn;enne seide he to Peter: &laquo;A, Peter, miht &thorn;ou not wake wi&thorn; me on houre?  Wake&thorn;, he seide, and preye&thorn;, &thorn;at &yogh;e ne falle in no temptacion.&raquo;  And he wente eft a&yogh;eyn, &amp; &thorn;enne fond he Orisoun, [&] a no&thorn;ur suster of &thorn;e hous &thorn;at hette Deuocion, and &thorn;enne he seide: &laquo;Mi ffader, se&thorn;&thorn;e hit may non o&thorn;er beo bote &thorn;at I mot to-morwen ben honged on &thorn;e rode-tre and
dyen, beo hit as &thorn;ou wolt.&raquo;  And he com a&yogh;eyn to his disciples, and font hem
slepynge as he dude biforen.  And &thorn;enne wente he eft a&yogh;eyn and preyede as he
dude furst, &amp; &thorn;er he fond wi&thorn; Orisoun &thorn;reo of hire sustren, Contemplacion,
Leaunce, and Iubilacioun:
