&thorn;at sprong out of &thorn;i syde?  &para; Whi nul I beo &thorn;i derlyng, and loue &thorn;e ouer alle &thorn;ing, and comen to &thorn;i cluppyng, to cleuen in &thorn;in armes &dot; and cluppen &thorn;e swete?  A derwor&thorn;e lord &dot; muchel is &thorn;i myldeschupe, &thorn;at spraddest so &thorn;in armes &dot; bodiliche on Roode, and in toknyng of &thorn;at &dot; openest &thorn;i grace, &thorn;at sprad is so wyde &dot; wi&thorn; loueliche tollyng, &amp; open is and redi &dot; to alle &thorn;at in synne &dot; beo&thorn; gostliche storuen.  Clepe&thorn; hem to lyue &dot; and to loue-cosses, as Moder do&thorn; hire deore sone &dot; &thorn;at here&thorn; hit wepen:  Take&thorn; hit in hire armus &dot; and aske&thorn; him so sweteliche:  'Ho leof, ho lef!'  heo do&thorn; him hire bitwenen(!), 'ho wole be bi-clupped &dot; and cusse me swete; who ha&thorn; do my deore &dot; who ha&thorn; do &thorn;e so?'  Heo &yogh;eue&thorn; him hire pappe &dot; and stille&thorn; his teres.  &THORN;at pappe beo my lykyng, my mournyng my longyng, swete Ihesu heuene kyng:  to souken of my fulle; &thorn;at &thorn;orw &thorn;e speres openyng, in feole mennes gounyng, wi&thorn; dewyng of &thorn;i deore blood &dot; stille&thorn; alle bales.  And wher eny mon wene &thorn;at he schal &dot; haue part of &thorn;at ilke sok &dot; of &thorn;i deore herte &dot; in heuene-riche blisse, and &thorn;ere be &thorn;i derlyng, in &thorn;i deore cluppyng, bote he &thorn;e heere cluppe &dot; hongynge on Roode, and parte of &thorn;i passion &dot; &thorn;orw holy meditacion, wi&thorn; loue-lykynde &thorn;ou&yogh;t &dot; and reu&thorn;e of his herte? Nay, sikerliche nay, ne trouwe &thorn;at no mon!  &para; Whose euere wol haue part &dot; &thorn;er of &thorn;i blisse:  he mot dele wi&thorn; &thorn;e &dot; heer of &thorn;i pyne.  Nis he nou&yogh;t good felawe &dot; ne felauschupe wor&thorn;i:  &thorn;at nul scoten i &thorn;e los &dot; as i &thorn;e bi&yogh;ete.  Hym bihoue&thorn; scoten &dot; after his euen