</P><P>A Milde Marie &dot; moder of Merci, socour of serweful &dot; and cumfort of care: Nartou lodesterre to alle &thorn;o &thorn;at in &thorn;e s&eacute;&eacute; Of &thorn;is worldes anguissche &dot; seilen and faren?  &THORN;ou &thorn;at art qween of angeles, ladi of alle schaftes; to whom is bitakene &dot; &thorn;e cure and &thorn;e cumfort &dot; of hem &thorn;at hem felen &dot; caytif wrecches, &para; &yogh;e &thorn;at in hor owne e&yogh;en &dot; seon hem-self wrecches, and sechen &thorn;in helpe &dot; wi&thorn; trust hope of herte; in &thorn;in aduocatye is put &dot; &thorn;e cause of vre sunnes, to stonden at domesday &dot; vr aller Iugges mooder, in help &amp; in Meyntenaunce &dot; of vre soule-hele. &para; &THORN;enk heer on &thorn;is wrecche &dot; Moder and Mayden, &thorn;at falle&thorn; &thorn;e tofote &dot; in hope of &thorn;in helpe, cryinde reu&thorn;ely &dot; after &thorn;i grace.  Pese me ladi, for &thorn;i muchele merci, to &thorn;i derwor&thorn;e sone &dot; &thorn;at Ichaue wi&thorn; sunne &dot; schomeliche and lihtliche &dot; so fele tyme a-gulte.  &para; Mi sunnes ben so gastliche &dot; grisliche and grete; make&thorn; me so wlatsum &dot; and stinkinde foule:  &thorn;at I ne dar him neih&yogh;en &dot; ne folwe my neode.  I haue wi&thorn; hem willes &dot; my soule forschupped:  from &thorn;e liknesse of god &dot; to &thorn;e deuel of helle; wra&thorn;&thorn;ed haue I willes &dot; &thorn;orw ful&thorn;e of my sunne &dot; mi makere mi buggere &dot; &thorn;at bou&yogh;te me so deore:  wi&thorn; his derwor&thorn;e de&thorn; &dot; from &thorn;raldam of helle; &thorn;at wolde ra&thorn;er suffre &dot; to dyen on Roode, &thorn;en to &thorn;olien in his siht &dot; &thorn;e wlatynge of sunne.  &para; Him-self sou&yogh;te my pes &dot; in myn owne gultes, as his hedde be &thorn;e gult &dot; moni tyme and ofte:  wi&thorn; sturyng of my concience &dot; &amp; preching of wyse; wi&thorn; hard wrake &thorn;at I sau&yogh; &dot; of o&thorn;er mennes sunnes; wi&thorn