truifle &dot; of vnsittyng &thorn;ing:  &thorn;en mony a foul sunne &dot; in siht of god almi&yogh;ti. &para; More him delyted &dot; forte enbrace Mock, and styngk of worldliche Mok &dot; &thorn;at gyle&thorn; so foule, &thorn;en ba&thorn;en in &thorn;e lykyng &dot; &amp; in &thorn;e loue-cluppyng, in &thorn;e brennynge loue &dot; of &thorn;e holygost.  &para; Al-beo &thorn;at on defendet &dot; and a&yogh;eyn &thorn;e lawe, and &thorn;at o&thorn;ur nomeliche &dot; I-&yogh;iuen vs in heste.  &THORN;at on is wonnen wi&thorn; swynk &dot; &amp; wi&thorn; muchel anguissche, and ende&thorn; atte laste &dot; wi&thorn; &yogh;eldyng of wreche; Trauayle &thorn;e wynnyng, drede in &thorn;e keping, serwe in &thorn;e leosyng &dot; and helle at &thorn;e ende.  &para; &THORN;at o&thorn;ur nis not so deore a-bouht &dot; bute is ful muche menskeful, wi&thorn; waxinde likyng &dot; &amp; bodiliche fyndyng, &amp; bringe&thorn; atte laste &dot; endeles blisse.</P><P>God sei&thorn; hit him-self &dot; &thorn;at hose seche&thorn; him furst, &amp; ouer al o&thorn;ur &thorn;ing &dot; aske&thorn; his blisse, al &thorn;at him be-houe&thorn; &dot; to bodiliche neode, schal be graunted &thorn;e[r]-wi&thorn; &dot; and &yogh;iuen in &thorn;at boone &mdash; Luc.:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Querite primum regnum dei &amp;c.</FOREIGN> // &THORN;is is he &thorn;at al day &dot; torne&thorn; god his hindewine, and hertliche loute&thorn; &dot; to cluppe worldes dweole.  &para; &THORN;is is &thorn;at blynde wrecche &dot; &thorn;at in his owne e&yogh;en Wene&thorn; him so vertuous &dot; &amp; is ful of vices; leete&thorn; him feir and freoly &dot; and ha&thorn; &thorn;e deueles liknesse; and wene&thorn; &thorn;at he beo witti &dot; and al ful of slei&yogh;&thorn;e:  and loke&thorn; on his chaffare &dot; &thorn;at he is afolte, &thorn;at sold ha&thorn; his soule &dot; for stinkynde lustes, and chaunge&thorn; god for &thorn;e deuel &dot; and heuene for helle.  He halt him ful dou&yogh;ti, stalwor&thorn;e &amp; hardi, and al day is ouercomen &dot; of him &thorn;at ha&thorn; no mi&yogh;te Forte wi&thorn;-stonde &thorn;e moste wrecche of &thorn;e world:  &thorn;at wolde a&yogh;eyn him fihte.  He lete&thorn; him gentil &dot; and is &thorn;e deueles &thorn;ral, and deme&thorn; hem wrecches &dot; and make&thorn; hem his harlotes, &thorn;at ben so gentil of blod &dot; &thorn;at god is heore fader.  &THORN;us he loke&thorn; him-self &dot; wi&thorn; a fals e&yogh;e, seo&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;at is nou&yogh;t &dot; and deme&thorn; al wrong.  Hit is &thorn;e deueles Mirour &dot; &thorn;at he in loke&thorn;, and &thorn;e fendes argumens &dot; &thorn;at him &thorn;inke&thorn; resouns, &thorn;at he bobbe&thorn; him wi&thorn; &dot; and lede&thorn; as him lyke&thorn;.&raquo;  A Ihesu Crist &thorn;in ore, hou schal I euer dry&yogh;en &dot; to &thorn;enken on &thorn;i domes:  a&yogh;eynes my gultes &dot; &thorn;at alle &thorn;yne schaftes &dot; &thorn;us harde mouwen acusen?  And not onliche &thorn;us, but &yogh;it mowe &thorn;ei cri&yogh;en &dot; and siggen in heore wyse:  &para; &laquo;&THORN;ees is &thorn;e deueles Maumet, &thorn;at ha&thorn; vs alle wrongliche Vsed in his werkes &dot; a&yogh;eynes vr kuynde.  He hedde godes liknesse &dot; and torned him-self out of &thorn;at In to &thorn;e liknesse &dot; of vch of vs alle; he is more eor&thorn;ly &dot; &thorn;en euer was eor&thorn;e, fikelore &thorn;en &thorn;e wynt, more veyn &thorn;en is &thorn;e eir, hattore in his lustes &dot; &thorn;en is &thorn;e fuir &thorn;at brenne&thorn;; hardore &thorn;en eny ston &dot; of wikkede herte:  a&yogh;ein his euencristne &dot; &thorn;at Crist representen; caldore of charite &dot; &thorn;en forst in his kuynde.  &para; What schal I more siggen?  he ne dredde not god &dot; ne mon he ne louede, but mengede his owne wikkednesse &dot; among moni o&thorn;ure, and dude &thorn;at in him was &dot; ladde hem his weies, and was to hem ensaumple &dot; and ledere to synne, wi&thorn; vnclene speches &dot; wi&thorn; lecherous lokynges, wi&thorn; schrewede dedes &dot; and mony lu&thorn;er leetes.  &para; Ne &thorn;hou&yogh;te him nou&yogh;t inouh &dot; &thorn;at godes de&thorn; on Roode Weore lost anontes him-self &dot; but anontes mony mo, and dude &thorn;at in him was &dot; as &thorn;e deueles promotour &dot; and godes oune traytor, to leden hem to sunne.  He bar him as he weore a god &dot; si&thorn;en &thorn;at he nolde Beo ilad bi godes wille &dot; ne bi no lawe, but as him lyked him-self &dot; a&yogh;eyn godes hestes Strayen out of lawe &dot; in wrong and in outrage, as mon al laweles:  &amp; don what him luste.  &para; &YOGH;if God ne dude for him &dot; al &thorn;at he wolde:  he gruyned a&yogh;eynes him &dot; as &thorn;au&yogh; he weore his knawe; and &yogh;if he eny tyme &dot; letted for [t]o


<PB N="2: 351">

sunne, hit was not for godes loue &dot; but for Monnes drede, or for bodiliche harm: or worldliche enchesun.  Bo&thorn;e of goode and of euel:  he wolde be loued, as &thorn;ei&yogh; he weore god self &dot; of whom alle &thorn;ing &thorn;at is, bo&thorn;e goode an vuel, is ordeynt for goode.  &para; What schal I of him &dot; more speke?  his pruide passe&thorn; Lucifer &dot; &thorn;at fel into helle; his gult Adames gult &dot; &thorn;at cast him out of paradis, and nou&yogh;t onliche him &dot; but alle monkuynde.  For &thorn;ey hedde muchel &thorn;at hem drowe &dot; to be proud offe, and he nedde but wrecchednesse:  &thorn;at scholde him wi&thorn;drawe.&raquo; Allas my foule ful&thorn;e:  and my muchel vnsleih&thorn;e!  What schal I nou to rede? whoder schal I now gon?  Wher schal I me beo-turnen &dot; nou alle &thorn;ing is &thorn;us risen &dot; a&yogh;eynes me one:  and wondre&thorn; &thorn;us on me?  &para; A&yogh;eynes alle schaftes:  haue I mis-taken, and my deore lord god:  lu&thorn;urliche dispiset, and alle his holy angeles:  greuousliche I-erred, and alle his holy halewen:  foule deshonoured, and myn euencristne:  in mony maner greued, and alle creatures:  haue I mis-vset, Anselmus.  A serwe and sikyng, cri&yogh;ing &amp; gronyng, wher be &yogh;e ryue:  &yogh;if &yogh;e here faylen?  &para; wher be &yogh;e feruent:  &yogh;if &yogh;e heere slaken?  Nou ne wot I whoderward &dot; I may me best bi-tornen, ffor I haue maked me fon:  in alle kunnes halue.  &para; Allas allas my lord god &dot; stured is to wra&thorn;&thorn;e, and no &thorn;ing ne haue I me laft &dot; &thorn;at al nis offendet:  &thorn;at scholde me helpe &dot; or eny good wille.  &para; &YOGH;if I ha wra&thorn;&thorn;ed &thorn;e sone, nis &thorn;e moder erred?  And &yogh;if &thorn;e Mooder be wro&thorn;, hou is &thorn;e sone quemed?  Who schal pese me wi&thorn; &thorn;e sone &dot; &yogh;if &thorn;e Moder beo my fo?  &para; Or who schal me geten &thorn;e Moder loue &dot; &yogh;if &thorn;e sone me hate?  &para; But deore lord of Merci &dot; &thorn;at art al merci, and &thorn;ou his deore Mooder &dot; &thorn;at art ful of grace: &yogh;if I haue ow bo&thorn;e a-gult &dot; ne be &yogh;e ful of Merci?  And wherto schulde merci &dot; &yogh;if gultus ne weore?  &para; Schal &thorn;e Malice of myn euel &dot; passen oure goodnesse? or alle myne sunnes:  ben more &thorn;en oure Milce?  &para; Ne art &thorn;ou lord bi-come mon &dot; and taken hast vr kuynde?  And &thorn;ou my deore ladi, bicomen art his Mooder?  &para; and hast al &thorn;i menske &dot; in heuene &amp; in eor&thorn;e, for resun of sunful &dot; and wreche to slaken?  &para; &THORN;ou lord bicome mon &dot; and a Mylde Maidenes barn, &thorn;at hard de&thorn; and schendful:  &thorn;oledest for &thorn;yn enemys; and &thorn;ou his deore Mooder &dot; wi&thorn; Maydenes menske, &thorn;e swerd of &thorn;i peyne:  &thorn;urlede &thorn;i soule &mdash; <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">animam tuam pertransiuit gladius.</FOREIGN>  And &thorn;at wolde &yogh;e &thorn;ole &dot; for Merci al-one:  to sechen hem &thorn;at weoren at-rei&yogh;t &dot; and drawen hem &thorn;at fledden.  &para; And I &thorn;at seche Merci &dot; and truste in &yogh;or Merci, and knoweleche my gult &dot; wi&thorn; sore herte-sykes, schulde fayle Merci &dot; &thorn;er welle is of Merci, &thorn;at is to alle synful &dot; so ryf and so large? &para; Wher is &thorn;enne &thorn;at word &dot; of cumfort &amp; blisse, &thorn;at &thorn;ou seidest &thorn;i-self &dot; derwor&thorn;e lord:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Nolo mortem peccatoris,</FOREIGN> &laquo;I nul not, &thorn;ou seist, &thorn;e de&thorn; of &thorn;e synful, but I wole he turne &dot; and stunte of his sunne, and ryse to my grace &dot; in lyf wi&thorn;-outen ende&raquo;.  And &thorn;at also &thorn;ou seist:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">In quacumque hora ingemuerit, saluus erit,</FOREIGN> &laquo;Whon so euere &thorn;e sunful &dot; for&thorn;inke&thorn; his sunne, &amp; wilne&thorn; for to stunten, anon he schal be saued&raquo;?  &para; Ne seidest &thorn;ou not lord &dot; to &thorn;e &thorn;eef on Roode, &thorn;at euer se&thorn;&thorn;en he cou&thorn;e &dot; hedde I-vsed &thorn;ef&thorn;e, &thorn;at in &thorn;e selue day &dot; he scholde ben in blisse?  and for no more decert &dot; but for he kneu&yogh; his gultes, and &thorn;e for his saueour &dot; &amp; asked &thorn;i Merci?  Ne was he put in no delay &dot; to ligge longe in peyne, but seidest so redily &dot; wi&thorn; so mylde steuene:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Hodie mecum eris in paradyso.</FOREIGN>  Nart &thorn;ou derwor&thorn;e lord &dot; &thorn;e Merciable ffader, &thorn;at &thorn;ou liknest &thorn;e to &dot; as


<PB N="2: 352">

telle&thorn; &thorn;e gospel, &para; &thorn;at whon so euere &thorn;e lu&thorn;er sone &dot; beo he neuer so gulti, &thorn;enke&thorn; in his herte &dot; to seche &thorn;i Merci:  anon &thorn;ou seost him a-fer &dot; in &thorn;at ilke &thorn;ou&yogh;t, and eornest a&yogh;eynest him &dot; wonderliche swi&thorn;e, and er he speke eny word &dot; but in &thorn;e &thorn;ou&yogh;t al-one, so &thorn;at hit be studefast &dot; and wil for to rysen, &para; &thorn;ou fallest aboute his nekke &dot; and cluppest him &amp; cussest, wi&thorn; chere ful blisful &dot; &amp; welcomest him hom, and clepest alle frendes &dot; and makest a feste, slest &thorn;e fatte feste-calf &dot; for &thorn;i sone sake, and biddest hem beo glade &dot; and bli&thorn;e blissen wi&thorn; &thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;i sone is founden &dot; &thorn;at &thorn;ou heddest loren &mdash; <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Occurrit filio prodigo videns eum a longe.</FOREIGN>  And whon &thorn;ow heng on Rode &dot; preyedest to &thorn;i ffader &dot; for &thorn;at ilke traytors &dot; &thorn;at duden &thorn;e to &thorn;e de&thorn;:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Pater ignosce illis, quia nesciunt quid faciunt.</FOREIGN>  And hedden alle Merci &dot; &thorn;at hit wolden asken; and of alle &thorn;ing &dot; most was &thorn;i &yogh;ernyng, &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolden eny wey &dot; &thorn;i merci vnderfonge.  &THORN;at Merci is so plentiuous &dot; so redi and so large:  profred and presed &dot; euer ar men hit asken.  For asken hit ne mai me not &dot; ne haue &thorn;at ilke grace, but &thorn;ou hit specialich &dot; put hit in vr wille.  And &yogh;it of alle &thorn;inge &dot; &thorn;en furstest &thorn;ou most &dot; aftur heor soulus &dot; &thorn;at merci for-soken.  Ne art &thorn;ou lord vr fader, and maked vs hast &thorn;in eires &dot; of &thorn;i grete blisse, and in &thorn;e pater noster &dot; biddest clepe &thorn;e so, and &thorn;at we asken of &thorn;e &dot; al &thorn;at vs like&thorn;, and &thorn;at not luitel &dot; but al hol &thorn;i-seluen, wi&thorn; al &thorn;at vs nede&thorn; &dot; to bodi and to soule?  &para; Hou schulde euere &thorn;e child &dot; failen of his askyng:  anentes such a ffader &dot; &thorn;at muchel more loue&thorn; &thorn;e child, &thorn;en he do&thorn; his owne bodi &dot; or dee&thorn; &thorn;e child him-seluen?  Nai sikerliche nay &dot; ne may he neuer faylen Of &thorn;at or better &thorn;erfore, but &yogh;if hit beo mis-asked.  &para; And al-beo &thorn;ou vr ffader &dot; Lord in persone, of &thorn;e ffader &thorn;ou art bicome vr bro&thorn;er &dot; in persone of Crist; vr Iuge &amp; vr domes-mon &dot; &thorn;at al &thorn;e world schal demen, art bi-comen vr bro&thorn;er &dot; of flesch and of blod.  &para; And sei[st] derwor&thorn;e lord &dot; &thorn;orw &thorn;e prophete, as fader al ful of loue &dot; wordes so swete: <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Numquid potest mater obliuisci filii vteri sui:  &amp; si illa obliuiscatur, ego non obliuiscar tui,</FOREIGN> &para; &laquo;&THORN;ou&yogh; &thorn;e moder mi&yogh;te for-&yogh;eten &dot; &thorn;e child &thorn;at heo bar, &thorn;ou ne mai&yogh;t for&yogh;ite mon &dot; &thorn;at wole to &thorn;e callen&raquo;; but seist &thorn;at al &thorn;i likynge &dot; &amp; al &thorn;i delices, euer is wi&thorn; vs for to wone &dot; and dwelle wi&thorn; mon &mdash; Salomon:  <FOREIGN
LANG="LAT">Delicie mee, esse cum filiis hominum.</FOREIGN>
</P><P>A &thorn;ou Blisful moder &dot; &thorn;at art vr oune Moder, &thorn;ou ne askest neuer wreche &dot; of no monnus sunnes, but were &thorn;e gult neuer so gret &dot; ne sunnes so monye, askest ay merci &dot; wi&thorn; moderliche reu&thorn;e; and &thorn;erfore bicome &thorn;ou &dot; Ihesu Cristes moder, &amp; moder of sunfole &dot; to bringen hem to grace.  &para; How scholde I desafyen &dot; to fallen in &yogh;or grace:  &thorn;at am &yogh;ou bo&thorn;e so sibbe &dot; &yogh;oure sone and &yogh;or bro&thorn;ur, and &thorn;ou lord my Iuge &dot; and myn oune bro&thorn;er, &para; and &thorn;ou ladi my Moder &dot; and my Iugges Modur, and of &thorn;e selue Iuge &dot; asignet to my counseil, to be myn aduocatrix &dot; beo-fore him in &thorn;e dom!  &para; Wher may be grace &dot; &yogh;if heer beo reddour; or eny hope founden &dot; &yogh;if hit heere fayle?  hou scholde I euer dreden &dot; to fynden alle fauour, and vnimete merci &dot; bi-fore so sib a Iuge, &para; &thorn;at haue&thorn; me so frendly &dot; &yogh;if &thorn;at I seche merci &dot; while tyme is of merci &dot; bi-tau&yogh;t so leof an helpe?  &para; Who schal my cause sauen &dot; &yogh;if heo ne may suffisen, &thorn;at ha&thorn; hit vndertaken &dot; &thorn;at and alle suche, and ha&thorn; hit of offyse &dot; for sunfol to causen: and is &thorn;e Iuge hire owne &dot; to for&thorn;eren al hir wille?</P>

