</P><P>LAdi Milde Marie &dot; Mooder of Merci, help of alle helplese &dot; and sunful of hele, socour of alle serwe &dot; &amp; boote of alle bale, to alle &thorn;at trusten in &thorn;e &dot; and sechen &thorn;in helpe: &para; help me Marie &dot; milde queene, ladi of heuene ... Emperisse and Mayden &dot; &amp; Godus deore Mooder.  Derwor&thorn;e ladi &dot; for to saue synful: Ihesu Crist bicom &thorn;i sone &dot; and dude &thorn;e &thorn;at menske; ffor vre sake weore &thorn;ou maad &dot; Maiden Godes Mooder.  Neore &thorn;ow nou&yogh;t as &thorn;ou art &dot; hi&yogh;ed ouer alle, qween of alle blisse: &yogh;if synful ne weore.  For-&thorn;i ou&yogh;ten sunful &dot; calle to &thorn;e sikerly, for whom &thorn;ou hast &thorn;in hey&yogh;nesse &dot; and &thorn;i muchele grace.  &para; Maiden and Moder &thorn;ou art: and his Mooder &thorn;ou art, his hondewerk &thorn;ou art &dot; his spouse and his dou&yogh;ter: his &thorn;at welde and wrou&yogh;te &dot; alle maner schaftes, &thorn;at regne&thorn; ay in blisse &dot; wi&thorn;-outen eny ende. &para; A swete ladi Marie &dot; muchel is &thorn;at menske: euer to ben in blisse &dot; such a sones Mooder, wi&thorn; al hol Maydenhod &dot; and Maydenes menske; and hast him so in baundoun &dot; and al at &thorn;i wille: &thorn;at he wole al &thorn;at &thorn;ou wolt &dot; ouer-al be for&thorn;ed.  And forte schewen vs &thorn;is &dot; he streihte &thorn;e his Riht arm &dot; as he heng on Roode &dot; and bouwede touward &thorn;e &dot; his derwor&thorn;e hed &dot; as &yogh;if he seide to &thorn;e: &laquo;Moder al &thorn;at &thorn;ou wolt &dot; schal ben at &thorn;i wille&raquo;.  &para; A swete ladi &dot; whi ne haue I euere &dot; by-fore myn herte ei&yogh;en &dot; &yogh;oure &thorn;reo serwes: &thorn;i sone i-streyht on Roode &dot; &thorn;orw-driuen feet and hondes &dot; wi&thorn; Irene nayles, blodi his syde; and &thorn;ou stode him bi &dot; and seynt Ion &thorn;e Ewangelist, weopynde on ei&thorn;er half &dot; wi&thorn; serewhful sykes.  &para; Whi ne bi-holde I euere &dot; &thorn;is in myn herte, and &thorn;enke &thorn;at hit was for me &dot; and for o&thorn;ur sunfol, &thorn;at he rudde out of helle &dot; and &yogh;af vs heuene-blisse?  &para; &THORN;is &thorn;ou&yogh;t wolde sikerliche &dot; cundle a brennynde loue; &thorn;at weore &thorn;e herte neuer so cold &dot; ne schulde neuer sunne &dot; ben folfuld in dede &dot; &thorn;er [&thorn;at] &thorn;ou&yogh;t ware.
